rComments: I am simple. She gives me an A then I give her an A. Warning: she doesn't really care about U.

Hua is one of the best profs I have ever met at UofT! She is super nice and caring. As long as you are willing to devote enough time to this course, you will do well. Also, Hua often offers students with extra info outside the textbook, which made her lectures interesting. The class activities are usually well-designed.

She is a nice prof. This course is textbook heavy. You must have at least read over the textbook readings in order to do okay on her 3 multiple choice tests. She does several interactive group activities and shows videos which is nice in the midst of having other heavy courses!
Felt like I was back in high school because of the way lectures were taught - reading from the slides, games, movies
I got A+ for her class. Her lectures help you to  understand better on textbook materials, and she give fair mark for the effort you have done on group project!  good prof!!!!!!

Hua knows what she is talking about, but you have to make sure you understand the material. If you do not, then just ask. The exams can be a bit tough, but if you understood the material, you will be just fine. Do not feel afraid to ask her something during the exam. She is very helpful in guiding you to the right direction.

rComments: After completing her course, if you were consistently prepared throughout the term, you'll know why Hua is one of my all-time favourite lecturers.

Her lectures are not bad but have nothing to do with the textbook or her exam, which is all multiple choices what require you to MEMORIZE the textbook. Good thing though is if u do read and at least try to remember the materials from the text then u will be fine on the tests. Also she gives fairly decent grades on assignments.
